As Cody gingerly detached the jackal's jaws from his leg, wincing in pain, he realized that he felt better than he would have expected – better, in fact, than he had in years. He straightened, stretching his arms out a little, and pondered the feeling for a moment. “Guess I'm getting a little bit of the old vigor back,” he remarked. He smiled a little. “Can't say I mind.” He stepped into the room, ignoring Lulu as she messily devoured the jackal.
